Martina tried to perform the following division and reduce to lowest terms:

$\blueE{\dfrac{-2x-8}{x^2+2x-15}} \div\maroonE{\dfrac{x+4}{x^2-6x+9}}$

This is her work:

>Rewriting the dividend: $\blueE{\dfrac{-2x-8}{x^2+2x-15}} =\dfrac{-2(x+4)}{(x+5)(x-3)}$

>Rewriting the divisor: $\maroonE{\dfrac{x+4}{x^2-6x+9}}=\dfrac{x+4}{(x-3)^2}$

>Finding excluded values: $x\neq -4$ and $x\neq 3$

>Dividing and reducing to lowest terms:

>$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\blueE{\dfrac{-2x-8}{x^2+2x-15}} \div\maroonE{\dfrac{x+4}{x^2-6x+9}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-2(x+4)}{(x+5)(x-3)}\div\dfrac{x+4}{(x-3)^2}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-2(x+4)}{(x+5)(x-3)}\cdot\dfrac{(x-3)^2}{x+4}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-2\cancel{(x+4)}\cancel{(x-3)}(x-3)}{(x+5)\cancel{(x-3)}\cancel{(x+4)}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-2(x-3)}{x+5}
\end{align}$

**What mistake did Martina make?**

[[☃ radio 1]]

Milas tried to perform the following division and reduce to lowest terms:

$\blueE{\dfrac{x^2+12x+36}{x+8}} \div\maroonE{\dfrac{3x+18}{x+2}}$

This is his work:

>Rewriting the dividend: $\blueE{\dfrac{x^2+12x+36}{x+8}} =\dfrac{(x+6)^2}{x+8}$

>Rewriting the divisor: $\maroonE{\dfrac{3x+18}{x+2}}=\dfrac{3(x+6)}{x+2}$

>Finding excluded values: $x\neq -8$ and $x\neq -2$

>Dividing and reducing to lowest terms:

>$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\blueE{\dfrac{x^2+12x+36}{x+8}} \div\maroonE{\dfrac{3x+18}{x+2}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(x+6)^2}{x+8}\div\dfrac{3(x+6)}{x+2}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(x+6)^2}{x+8}\cdot\dfrac{x+2}{3(x+6)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(x+6)\cancel{(x+6)}(x+2)}{3(x+8)\cancel{(x+6)}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(x+6)(x+2)}{3(x+8)}
\end{align}$

**What mistake did Milas make?**

