Michelle tried to perform the following division and reduce to lowest terms:

$\blueE{\dfrac{-4x+20}{x^2-x-12}} \div\maroonE{\dfrac{x^2-25}{x+3}}$

This is her work:

>Rewriting the dividend: $\blueE{\dfrac{-4x+20}{x^2-x-12}} =\dfrac{-4(x+5)}{(x+3)(x-4)}$

>Rewriting the divisor: $\maroonE{\dfrac{x^2-25}{x+3}}=\dfrac{(x+5)(x-5)}{x+3}$

>Finding excluded values: $x\neq \pm5$, $x\neq -3$, and $x\neq 4$

>Dividing and reducing to lowest terms:

>$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\blueE{\dfrac{-4x+20}{x^2-x-12}} \div\maroonE{\dfrac{x^2-25}{x+3}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-4(x+5)}{(x+3)(x-4)}\div\dfrac{(x+5)(x-5)}{x+3}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-4(x+5)}{(x+3)(x-4)}\cdot\dfrac{x+3}{(x+5)(x-5)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-4\cancel{(x+5)}\cancel{(x+3)}}{\cancel{(x+3)}(x-4)\cancel{(x+5)}(x-5)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-4}{(x-4)(x-5)}
\end{align}$

**What mistake did Michelle make?**

