Adriel tried to perform the following division and reduce to lowest terms:

$\blueE{\dfrac{-x+1}{3x-6}} \div\maroonE{\dfrac{x^2-1}{x+4}}$

This is his work:

>Rewriting the dividend: $\blueE{\dfrac{-x+1}{3x-6}} =\dfrac{-(x+1)}{3(x-2)}$

>Rewriting the divisor: $\maroonE{\dfrac{x^2-1}{x+4}}=\dfrac{(x+1)(x-1)}{x+4}$

>Finding excluded values: $x\neq \pm1$, $x\neq -4$, and $x\neq 2$

>Dividing and reducing to lowest terms:

>$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\blueE{\dfrac{-x+1}{3x-6}} \div\maroonE{\dfrac{x^2-1}{x+4}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-(x+1)}{3(x-2)}\div\dfrac{(x+1)(x-1)}{x+4}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-(x+1)}{3(x-2)}\cdot\dfrac{x+4}{(x+1)(x-1)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-\cancel{(x+1)}(x+4)}{3(x-2)\cancel{(x+1)}(x-1)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-(x+4)}{3(x-2)(x-1)}
\end{align}$

**What mistake did Adriel make?**

